Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AskData
    The AskData class is the class that extends the JPanel and ask the user for their name.
    Critter
    The Critter class is the class that creates the actual critter.
    CritterHome
    The CritterHome class is the class that creates the home of the Critter which has a critter.
    CritterSitterApp
    The CritterSitterApp is the driver class that creates CritterSitterApp as well as executes the program.
    Doctor
    The Doctor class is the class that creates the doctor.
    Food
    The Food class is the class that makes each individiual food, assigns the name, price, food group, nutrient value and icon.
    GroceryStore
    The GroceryStore class is the class that has the grocery store and has different foods for the user to buy and feed their critter.
    HighScores
    The HighScores class is the class that generates and outputs the high scores of the top 10 scores to an output file.
    Instructions
    The Instructions class displays game instructions to the user using a tabbed pane.
    MainMenu
    The MainMenu class is the main menu screen where the user can choose to either play the game, read the instructions, see the high scores or quit the game.
    PrintHighScores
    The PrintHighScores class is used to print the high scores on a piece of paper when the user when clicks the "Print" button in the high scores class.
    Recreation
    The Recreation class is the class that lets the user play the 'mini-game' and each difficulty has a different and unique input screen.
    Sound
    The Sound class loops the background music.
    SplashScreen
    The SplashScreen class is the class that displays the splash screen animation when the program first executes.
